We talked with a Bristol Township district judge who served at Ground Zero in the wake of the September 11, 2001 attacks. 

Read that and more 20th anniversary coverage on LevittownNow.com this weekend.

node.text:
It was Sunday, January 19, 2014 when two officers arrived at Kelli Donlen’s Levittown home and knocked on the door.

At the time, she was awaiting the arrival of her 15-year-old nephew Zachary Gonzalez, who was out with friends, when she heard terrible news from the officers.

Donlen said she was told Zachary had died along Route 13 when he was struck by a Volkswagen.

Read more on LevittownNow.com...
